changes-to-save: These changes need to be saved:
set_reminder: Choose when you want to be reminded about
tt-autosave: Enable to automatically save whenever anything changes
tt-default-cons: Set the default constraints for random password generation
tt-epass-change: Change the encryption password for the store
tt-hide-vals: Hide values until they are hovered over. Use if someone might be looking over your shoulder
tt-lang-code: Enter the language code for a supported language (requires restart)
tt-last-change: Show when the last change happened
tt-opt-advice: Optimise the store by removing old actions. The cloud keeps a history of all changes from all clients, so that every client has a chance to see every change. This history can get quite long, so you may want to optimise it by removing the history. You should only do this if you are 100% certain that no client has local changes that may need to be saved to the cloud
tt-pass-chars: Enter the characters that are legal in passwords for this site. You can use character ranges like A-Z or 0-9
tt-reset-loc: Reset the local store. This will reset the local store from the cloud. Any local changes will be lost.
tt-set-epass: Change the encryption password for the store. This should be different to the password you use to log in to your cloud storage provider (e.g. Google). You should ensure that all clients up to date and you are safely connected to the internet before changing the password, or you may lose data. The encryption password is never saved, and there is no way to recover it if you lose it!
unreadable_local: Local store exists, but can't be read.
update-fail: Could not update from cloud store '$1'
url_required: A URL is required for a $1 store
